African contractor that supplies workers to Impala Platinum Ltd.
and Xstrata Plc, said a planned strike over pay by the National
Union of Mineworkers has been suspended pending further talks.  The strike, which was due to start with the night shift
yesterday, has been suspended while further discussions between
the company and union are held, Andre Oldknow, JICâ€™s director
